name: Treasurer Colleen Davis
tweet: Think of it this way: normally, if you lend someone money for a long period of time, you would expect them to pay you back more than if you lent them money for a short period of time. That isn't the case when the curve inverts. What other economic questions do you have? #netDE

name: Treasurer Colleen Davis
tweet: Lately, you've probably talk about the Yield Curve. So, what is it? It's a map of interest rates (yields) for the same investment over time. When the curve "inverts" it means that an investment in a short period, 2 years, may pay more than that of a long period, like 10 years.  https://t.co/oSC63joNgu
